The number_of_windows feature contained missing values represented by a dot (.). These values were first converted to NaN to enable numerical processing. The column was then cast to a numeric data type. Missing values were imputed using the median to reduce the influence of outliers and preserve dataset size.

Categorical features with binary values were encoded using domain-informed binary mapping. For the Garden variable, V (has garden) was encoded as 1 and O (no garden) as 0. For the Settlement variable, U (urban) was encoded as 1 and R (rural) as 0. This ensured compatibility with numerical analysis and machine learning algorithms while preserving semantic meaning.

Q1 = df['Building Dimension'].quantile(0.25) #calculating Q1
Q3 = df['Building Dimension'].quantile(0.75) #calculating Q3
IQR = Q3 - Q1 #calculating IQR

lower = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR #calculating lower bound
upper = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR #calculating upper bound

df['Building Dimension'] = df['Building Dimension'].clip(lower, upper) #handling outliers by capping

In[91]:
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, roc_auc_score

def evaluate_model(model, X_test, y_test):
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
    
    report = classification_report(y_test, y_pred, output_dict=True)
    auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob)
    
    return {
        'Precision': report['1']['precision'],
        'Recall': report['1']['recall'],
        'F1-score': report['1']['f1-score'],
        'ROC-AUC': auc
    }
In[92]:
results = {}

results['Logistic Regression'] = evaluate_model(lr, X_test, y_test)
results['Decision Tree'] = evaluate_model(dt, X_test, y_test)
results['Random Forest'] = evaluate_model(rf, X_test, y_test)
results['Gradient Boosting'] = evaluate_model(gb, X_test, y_test)

Four classification models were trained and evaluated. Logistic Regression achieved the highest F1-score and recall, indicating superior balance in identifying minority-class instances. Ensemble methods showed higher precision but suffered from reduced recall. Consequently, Logistic Regression was selected as the final model and further refined using threshold adjustment and hyperparameter tuning.
